	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's level dependant, and at level 52, it is 12 per tick.&nbsp;&nbsp;That means at level 60, it should be 18 per tick.  Basically, it is as follows<br><br>under 20 - 3 per tick<br>under 50 - 6 per tick<br>under 60 - 12 per tick<br>60 - 18 per tick (I'm not 60 so can't verify this, but the other 3 are acurate)<br><br>I've payed close attention to this because I normally always have one of the lich series up.  As for this item, the extra 12 regen at level 60 would allow an Iksar necromancer to keep Lich up while sitting without loosing any hp.  Add a high level regen, and Demi lich or Arch lich shouldn't drain much life at all.  However, I don't agree with people saying any item is for one class, many items can be used by several classes with really good results.<br><br>Xalion Buscador<br>52 Heretic (Iksar)<br>Knights of Reverence<br>Xev<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
